metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #16
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Continuum #104
metadata.description:
This project is the culmination of many generative art experiments I have run throughout 2022. It relies heavily on the random walks through color and space techniques I have been working with, but also introduces other elements related to 2D and 3D rotation, framing and grains.

Continuum began as an abstract composition made up of a set of interacting elements against a background. This is still true. However, in my own mind, I have come to consider many Continuum pieces as peculiar, stylized observations of massive futuristic spacial, or quantum, constructions. Maybe even involving a wormhole through the fabric of space-time for some civilization well past 1 on the Kardashev scale. At the center is an erratic crystalline form, which is fed by power trains, and all around is a massive multicolored rotating containment structure.

Aside from the standard, inverse, threshold and washed types, the most defining trait of each composition is the “Back Style” which relates to a point of construction, activity or deconstruction of these structures. This is further refined by the panel style, the panel density and the rotation level. The other traits largely relate to color variability and aesthetics. 

This work has been coded using p5.js, and half of all royalties from the primary, and secondary, sales are assigned to the processing foundation.

Press s to download a 2400x2400 pixel image.

This work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License.

metadata.name: Para Metric #29
metadata.description: This collection of NFTs is based on an elementary mathematical principle; a parametric equation. Despite the simplicity of the principle, the results are simply stunning. All kinds of intricate shapes and patterns are formed by drawing random dots a parametric equation solely based on sines and cosines. Combined with a simple bright shape in the background, the art pieces are created. Every piece is highly unique can with different backgrounds and amount of shapes. I hope you enjoy the pieces!

metadata.name: Fractured Spectra v1.9 #9
metadata.description:
My continued exploration of color, shape, form, function, fractal chaos, order, and understanding of the mathematical beauty of nature to create beautiful, unique and colorful designs made up of translucent glassy elements. In this piece I explore symmetry and contrasting elements, suggesting a nearly impossible blown glass sculpture. Each unique rendering has a character of its own, some smooth and sensuous while others with sharp color and form changes, ragged edges, and chaotic beauty. Interactive with several user controls:

With the mouse:

Left click and drag to change the viewing angle
Right click and drag to change the view center
Mouse wheel to change the distance to the view center

With the keyboard:

Keys "," and "." (i.e. "<" and ">") change the rotation speed left or right. You can stop it entirely, or speed it up to what I consider a reasonable maximum, rotating to the left or to the right. Each time you press, it adjusts the rotation speed

Keys "a" "b" and "c": the lights always start in the same place, and each key controls one of the three lights, both position and intensity. It is deterministic from the initial start based upon the token: for a given token, after the initial run (or re-run) pressing "aaabbcabcabc" will give you the same sequence of lighting changes. This lets you choose your favorite and keep track of it.

metadata.name: I wish for the metaverse ... #169
metadata.description:
I WISH FOR THE METAVERSE TO RINSE OFF OF ME is a collection about both the power and the infirmity of affirmations. Shamanic, mantra-like, willful, affirmations seek to map a desired direction. That is, until time and mind get in the way.  Within brief, passing moments, our minds are able to manifest conflicting wishes—and do so via declarative, convincing statements. 
 
This work plays inside the chasm that divides intention and action. If we don’t know what we want, how can we act? Without the commitment of mind along the vast axis of time, our affirmations risk becoming sloganistic, simplistic, unrealistic—wavering proclamations that announce our vulnerability. 
 
Key words in these algorithmic affirmations shift over time to reflect the way our minds fluctuate. By shuffling words, this collection also explores our fluid relation to language. How to construct meaningful lives, when signification changes, moment to moment, within our minds? 
 
I WISH FOR THE METAVERSE TO RINSE OFF OF ME is a performance of fragility, which is where our humanity—and our beauty—abounds. 

-spacebar will pause the animation

-return will resume the animation

metadata.name: Ghost Friend #109
metadata.description:
Everyone dreams of a friend that would never leave them (we prefer to call it "haunting" around here), that could follow you around no matter where you go (even if it involves going through brick walls) while also being able to scare away their toughest enemies - and trust me, there's no better option than a ghost friend!

Each ghost is created exclusively with code (mostly in p5.js) without any assets and has a unique yet universally charming appearance 👻

Credit for visual inspiration goes to spooky project by watabo_shi, as well as ghostly artworks by Jordan Jenkins, Jonas Mosesson, Rytis, amy luo, Marvin Rudolph and others.

License: CC-BY-SA 4.0
